listing.overview: Work smarter and faster with the power of Butler, Trello’s built-in automation, added to your boards.
listing.description:
**Work smarter and faster with the power of Butler, Trello’s built-in automation, added to your boards.**

Let’s face it, inefficiencies get multiplied when team members have to do the same repetitive tasks. With Butler, anyone can create simple natural language commands to make work auto-magically happen on their boards, saving tons of time and bringing process to any team’s workflow.

Best of all, Butler is available to all users, and advanced features are included at no additional cost in Business Class, Enterprise, and Gold subscriptions. [Learn more](https://trello.com/pricing)

With Butler you can create:

- **Rules** - Set rules that trigger automatically when actions are performed on boards that perform predefined tasks.
- **Card Buttons** - Custom card buttons perform tasks and actions when clicked.
- **Board Buttons** - Board buttons execute tasks across an entire board.
- **Scheduled Commands** - Organize, clean up, and update boards at set dates and times so that you don’t need to think about it. (Available with Business Class, Enterprise, and Gold)
- **Date Commands** - Set commands to automatically trigger actions around upcoming or past due dates. (Available with Business Class, Enterprise, and Gold)

Butler can perform actions, such as:

- Moving, archiving, or copying cards
- Adding or removing labels, attachments, labels, and more
- Setting, changing, or updating due dates
- Adding, completing, or resetting checklists
- Joining, subscribing, and adding/removing members from cards
- Renaming cards, editing descriptions, adding comments
- Modifying, adding, or removing Custom Field data
- Sorting lists by a variety of criteria
- Interacting with related cards
- Sending emails (Available with Business Class, Enterprise, and Gold)
- Gets, posts, and puts to URLs (Available with Business Class, Enterprise, and Gold)
- And so much more!

Want to learn more about Butler? [Check out the Trello blog.](https://blog.trello.com/butler-power-up-trello-automation)

##Video##

[![Video](https://trello-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/5c754b933c3c6f6e427e8b16/5c8821e72fad5826106ab8a9/7bb8594495bc76252af7c02409ab15d7/ButlerTitleFrame.png)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0KxlGW-gzK0)

Note: video opens in a new tab.

listing.overview: BigPicture Gantt chart power-up for Project Portfolio Management. Structure your tasks on a timeline - calendar. Work like a pro in Trello!
listing.description:
**BigPicture** empowers you to dynamically manage project **Work Breakdown Structure**, **filter and display** the selected data the way you want it; **Milestones,  markers, critical path, progress and custom views** let you quickly evaluate your project status.

![Overview](https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/softwareplant-cdn/bigpicture/trello/icons/INTROTRELLOFILM-min.gif)
Enhance the project management experience using **BigPicture**, a **PPM Power-Up** tool. The top-selling Jira plugin is now available for Trello. Plan your tasks using marvelous and colorful Gantt charts, automate your work or keep track of all the changes using different modes. Create **dependencies or structure** your tasks using **drag&drop**.

#**With BigPicture you can:**

- Schedule your tasks using **drag&drop**
- **Automate** your work or work in **manual mode**
- Create advanced **Work Breakdown Structure**
- Link your tasks using **dependency links**
- **Customize** the view
- Add more tasks using **Artificial tasks**
- **Sort and group** your cards

![Grouping tasks](https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/softwareplant-cdn/bigpicture/trello/icons/GROUPLAND-min.gif)

![Grouping tasks](https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/softwareplant-cdn/bigpicture/trello/icons/LINKLAND-min.gif)

#**How does it work?**

**BigPicture** displays **Trello Cards** in a form of Tasks which can be easily allocated on the Gantt chart accompanied by the **WBS (Work Breakdown Structure)** panel. Since Cards are allocated to Boards, we could take an approach in which a Board represents a certain project. This Power-Up is capable of displaying a number of Cards from **multiple Boards** (projects) in form of Tasks on the **Gantt chart**.


![WorkBreakdownStructure](https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/softwareplant-cdn/bigpicture/trello/icons/BOARDLAND.gif)


#**Who is this for?**

Boost up your **Teams'** productivity and grow! Wheather your team is small or large take advantage of all Trello's features and combine it with professional tools.

Check BigPicture Power-Up [website](https://softwareplant.com/trello/), [documentation](https://wiki.softwareplant.com/display/DOCUMENTATION/About+BigPicture+Trello), [EULA](https://wiki.softwareplant.com/display/DOCUMENTATION/BigPicture+Trello+EULA) and [Privacy Policy](https://wiki.softwareplant.com/display/DOCUMENTATION/BigPicture+Trello+Privacy+Policy).

listing.description: Deadline lets you get the big picture with an instant overview of all your due dates sorted by priority. listing.description:
## Agile toolbox to manage your Sprints and make your life easier. 


**[Scrum by Vince](https://trello.vince.run/scrum)** is a Trello Power-Up that brings **the essential tools you need in a Scrum workflow to your board.** Thanks to a simple naming convention, Scrum by Vince helps to make your **process easier and more flexible.** Get your sprint ready, follow up the workload and the sprint completion.


If you work with/in a Dev team with Trello and Scrum, you may have to manage a lot of boards on different projects with different statuses. **Scrum by Vince helps you to organize your sprint boards** by using a nice and **clear board naming convention** for sprints projects and statuses.

- Adopt a clear naming convention for your sprint boards.

- See sprint status in the blink of an eye.

- Track your sprint’s burndown in real time.

[FAQ](https://help.vince.run)

[Discover Website](https://trello.vince.run/scrum)
